Ohk, hey everyone. I'm just curious. If you wait your script between procedures, does it make it less jagex detectable?
Like, would;
[code]program waitedScript;

const
Message1='Hai der';
Message2='Just clearing the debug.. Continuing on with script.';

procedure Hello;
begin
Writeln(Message1);
end;


begin
repeat
wait(4000);
clearDebug;
hello;
wait(2000);
clearDebug;
Writeln(Message2);
until(false)
end.[/code]

Be less detectable, then;
[code]program script;

const
Message1='Hai der!';
Message2='Just clearing the debug.. Continuing on with script.';

procedure Hello;
begin
Writeln(Message1);
end;


begin
repeat
clearDebug;
hello;
clearDebug;
Writeln(Message2);
until(false)
end.[/code]

Because it's waited.. And acts a bit more human speed?
